# Rule 3: Risk & Compliance Governance

## Core Principle

**CentralRiskManager is the SINGLE POINT OF AUTHORITY** for ALL trading decisions. No component can execute trades independently. All trades flow through the authorization pipeline.

---

## Authorization Pipeline (Phases 6-10)

```
FROM RULE 2: Strategy Signals
                ↓
PHASE 6: MULTI-STRATEGY COORDINATION
├── Component: StrategyManager
├── Responsibility: Aggregate signals, resolve conflicts
└── Output: List[TradingDecisionRequest]
                ↓
PHASE 7: PRE-TRADE COMPLIANCE 🔴
├── Component: PreTradeComplianceChecker
├── Responsibility: 7 regulatory checks
└── Output: ComplianceResult (approved/rejected)
                ↓
PHASE 8: RISK AUTHORIZATION ⭐
├── Component: CentralRiskManager
├── Authority: SINGLE POINT for ALL trades
├── Responsibility: 9 mandatory checks
└── Output: TradingAuthorization
                ↓
PHASE 9: CIRCUIT BREAKER 🔴
├── Component: TradingCircuitBreakers
├── Authority: SYSTEM_CONTROL
├── Responsibility: Catastrophic loss prevention
└── Output: CircuitBreakerStatus
                ↓
PHASE 10: POST-AUTHORIZATION
├── Component: CentralRiskManager
├── Responsibility: Final limits, audit record
└── Output: ValidatedAuthorization
                ↓
           → TO RULE 5: PHASE 11 (Execution)
```

