## Phase 8: Risk Authorization ⭐

### 9 Mandatory Authorization Checks

```python
async def authorize_trading_decision(self, request: TradingDecisionRequest) -> TradingAuthorization:
    # CHECK 1: Signal confidence (min 60%)
    if request.confidence < 0.60:
        return self._reject("Confidence below threshold")
    
    # CHECK 2: Cash availability (BUY)
    if request.side == 'buy' and required_cash > self.available_cash:
        return self._reject("Insufficient cash")
    
    # CHECK 3: Position availability (SELL)
    if request.side == 'sell' and request.quantity > current_position:
        return self._reject("No position to sell")
    
    # CHECK 4: Position size (max 10% of portfolio)
    if position_value > portfolio_value * 0.10:
        return self._reject("Position size exceeds limit")
    
    # CHECK 5: Concentration (max 15%)
    if concentration > 0.15:
        return self._reject("Concentration exceeds limit")
    
    # CHECK 6: Daily VaR (max 5%)
    if current_var > 0.05:
        return self._reject("Daily VaR exceeds limit")
    
    # CHECK 7: Strategy allocation (max 33%)
    if strategy_allocation > 0.33:
        return self._reject("Strategy allocation exceeds limit")
    
    # CHECK 8: Regime-adjusted scaling
    adjusted_quantity = request.quantity * regime_multiplier
    
    # CHECK 9: Emergency mode
    if self.emergency_mode:
        return self._reject("System in emergency mode")
    
    return TradingAuthorization(authorized=True, quantity=adjusted_quantity)
```

### Default Risk Limits

| Limit | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Max position size | 10% of portfolio |
| Max daily VaR | 5% |
| Max concentration | 15% per position |
| Max strategy allocation | 33% per strategy |
| Min signal confidence | 60% |

